summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Western Sahara, reaffirms its commitment to a just, lasting and mutually acceptable political solution providing for self-determination of the people of Western Sahara.
It calls on parties and States to cooperate with the UN to end the impasse and achieve progress towards a political solution.
Noting the release of 404 Moroccan prisoners of war by the POLISARIO Front, it calls for continued cooperation with the International Committee of the Red Cross.
Welcoming the appointment of Peter van Walsum as Secretary-General's Personal Envoy, it takes note of his recent consultations in the region.
The Security Council:
1. Reaffirms the need for full respect of military agreements with MINURSO regarding the ceasefire;
2. Calls on Member States to consider voluntary contributions for Confidence Building Measures;
3. Extends the mandate of MINURSO until 30 April 2006;
4. Requests a report from the Secretary-General on the situation before the end of the mandate period and a briefing from the Personal Envoy within three months;
5. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
